definitions.example: We had to scrub the seats for throw up when we left the dog in the car.

definitions.definition: To produce something new or unexpected.
definitions.example: This system has thrown up a few problems.

definitions.definition: To cause something such as dust or water to rise into the air.
definitions.example: The car wheels threw up a shower of stones.

definitions.definition: To display a gang sign using the hands
To enlarge, as a picture reflected on a screen.
